  "summary": "Dependency-confusion package exfiltrates host identifiers on install",
  "details": "@pluxee-connect/api-client@99.0.0 is a near-empty stub (only a 2-value ConsentsStatus enum) published at an inflated version under a scope mimicking Pluxee internal naming — the canonical dependency-confusion shape. On `npm install`, postinstall.js reads os.hostname(), os.userInfo().username, and process.version and beacons them via both HTTP GET and DNS lookup to a hardcoded interact.sh-style out-of-band collaborator domain (`d84t2rmqt3fpphmbii3gf9sdi63c3gkp7.oast.online`) at path `/poc?pkg=\u0026host=\u0026user=\u0026node=`. The beacon fires automatically on every install without consent and leaks installer-side identifiers to a third-party host, regardless of any 'PoC' framing.",
